data.title: QUETZAL Definition & Meaning
data.meta_description: Quetzal definition: any of several large Central and South American trogons of the genus Pharomachrus, having golden-green and scarlet plumage, especially P. mocino(resplendent quetzal ), the national bird of Guatemala. See examples of QUETZAL used in a sentence.
